The paper deals with relation extraction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category. The use of neural networks and attention mechanisms suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed approach involves the use of capsule networks, which are a relatively new type of neural network, indicating that the paper could also be classified under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
